info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 13 at 9:03PM MST until February 14 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 6 PM MST TUESDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 50 MPH with gusts up to 70 MPH possible. * WHERE...Central and Southern Laramie Range and adjacent Foothills, including Interstate 80 between Laramie and Cheyenne, and Interstate 25 near Bordeaux between Chugwater and Wheatland. * WHEN...3 AM MST until 6 PM MST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
